title: Joe Lovano on Newport Jazz Festival's legacy

description: Saxophonist Joe Lovano talks about playing at the Newport Jazz Festival with various groups and about the festival's legacy.  Lovano also talks about some of his favorite jazz albums that were recorded live at Newport. This In Person with JazzTimes interview took place backstage inside Fort Adams at the 2012 Newport Jazz Festival, where Lovano performed with Soundprints, the group he co-leads with Dave Douglas. Interview by Lee Mergner. Video by Melissa Mergner. Audio by Jen Kim. Special thanks to Carolyn McClair, Melanie Nanez, Dan Melnick, Deborah Ross and the staff of George Wein Productions.
